<!-- {"session_id":"04772a04-3750-4351-9415-cfd34a232cad","transcript_path":"/Users/yabo/.claude/projects/-Users-yabo-Documents-Code-phone-to-laptop/04772a04-3750-4351-9415-cfd34a232cad.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"Task","tool_input":{"description":"Reimplement test suite","prompt":"You are tasked with completely reimagining and reimplementing the test suite for this Telegram voice transcription bot. You have complete freedom to change, delete, update, and create new tests, folders, and structures.\n\n## Context from Previous Audit\n\nYour previous audit identified these critical issues:\n1. **Severe mock abuse** - Tests mock everything and validate nothing real\n2. **No actual transcription testing** - Whisper model is completely mocked\n3. **Command tests only verify mock calls** - No real functionality testing\n4. **Voice processing is 100% mocked** - No integration validation\n\nThe audit gave the test suite a 6.5/10 score, with service tests being excellent (9/10) but command tests (3/10) and transcription tests (4/10) being terrible due to mock abuse.\n\n## Your Mission\n\nYou have COMPLETE FREEDOM to:\n- Delete any existing test files that are beyond salvation\n- Create new test structure/folders as needed\n- Implement proper integration tests with real components\n- Add test helpers and utilities\n- Create test data generators (audio files, etc.)\n- Reorganize the entire test suite\n\n## Specific Requirements\n\n1. **Real Transcription Testing**\n   - Use actual Whisper models (tiny for speed)\n   - Generate or use real audio files\n   - Validate actual transcription output\n   - Test error cases with corrupted audio\n\n2. **Integration-First Testing**\n   - Use real ServiceContainer and services\n   - Only mock external dependencies (Telegram API)\n   - Test actual file I/O and state persistence\n   - Validate end-to-end workflows\n\n3. **Meaningful Test Coverage**\n   - Test actual business logic, not mock interactions\n   - Include error scenarios and edge cases\n   - Performance benchmarks for transcription\n   - Multi-language validation\n\n4. **Test Infrastructure**\n   - Audio file generators for testing\n   - Performance markers (slow, fast, integration)\n   - Proper fixtures for real components\n   - Test data management\n\n## Implementation Guidelines\n\n1. Start by analyzing the current test suite thoroughly\n2. Identify what to keep, fix, or completely rewrite\n3. Create a new test structure if needed\n4. Implement tests that actually validate functionality\n5. Ensure all tests are meaningful and test real behavior\n6. Add proper test documentation\n\n## Technical Constraints\n\n- Use `uv` for all Python operations (not pip)\n- Tests must use pytest\n- Follow the project's clean architecture\n- Maintain compatibility with existing code structure\n- Tests should be fast by default (use markers for slow tests)\n\n## Expected Deliverables\n\n1. A completely restructured test suite that:\n   - Actually tests real functionality\n   - Has minimal mock usage (only for external APIs)\n   - Includes real audio transcription tests\n   - Provides meaningful coverage metrics\n   - Is well-organized and maintainable\n\n2. Test utilities and helpers:\n   - Audio file generation\n   - Test data factories\n   - Integration test helpers\n   - Performance benchmarking tools\n\n3. Documentation:\n   - Test strategy document\n   - How to run different test suites\n   - Performance expectations\n   - Coverage goals\n\nRemember: The goal is to have tests that actually give confidence that the system works, not just that mocks return what they're told to return.\n\nBegin by exploring the current test suite, then proceed with your complete reimplementation. You have full autonomy to make any changes necessary to create a world-class test suite.","subagent_type":"python-test-auditor"},"tool_response":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Both pass, but 